## 2. Essential Commands Reference

Top 10 essential commands most frequently used by system administrators in production environments and exams.

| Action | Command |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Check Firewall Daemon Status** | `systemctl status firewalld` |
| **Start and Enable Firewall Daemon** | `systemctl enable --now firewalld` |
| **List All Currently Active Rules** | `firewall-cmd --list-all` |
| **List Active Zones and Bindings** | `firewall-cmd --get-active-zones` |
| **List All Predefined Services** | `firewall-cmd --get-services` |
| **Allow a Service (Temporary)** | `firewall-cmd --add-service=http` |
| **Allow a Port/Protocol (Permanent)** | `firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=8080/tcp` |
| **Remove a Service/Port Rule** | `firewall-cmd --permanent --remove-service=http` |
| **Apply Permanent Rules Instantly** | `firewall-cmd --reload` |
| **List Active Rich Rules Only** | `firewall-cmd --list-rich-rules` |

